You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Error

Bai Jamjuree ExtraLight Regular (BaiJamjuree-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree ExtraLight'.

Bai Jamjuree ExtraLight Italic (BaiJamjuree-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Bai Jamjuree Light Regular (BaiJamjuree-Light.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-Light', Everything looks good.

Bai Jamjuree Light Regular (BaiJamjuree-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree Light'.

Pass

Bai Jamjuree Light Italic (BaiJamjuree-LightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. Bai Jamjuree Light Italic (BaiJamjuree-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Bai Jamjuree Light Italic (BaiJamjuree-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Bai Jamjuree Medium Regular (BaiJamjuree-Medium.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-Medium', Everything looks good.

Pass

License text

This Font Software is licensed under the SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1. This license is available with a FAQ at: http://scripts.sil.org/OFL
, most common Monotype license test is:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Bai Jamjuree Medium Regular (BaiJamjuree-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree Medium'.

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Bai Jamjuree Medium Italic (BaiJamjuree-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Bai Jamjuree Medium Italic (BaiJamjuree-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree SemiBold'.

Bai Jamjuree SemiBold Italic (BaiJamjuree-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. Bai Jamjuree SemiBold Italic (BaiJamjuree-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Bai Jamjuree' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Bai Jamjuree SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

NID 6 is 'BaiJamjuree-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True
and should be:
Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True

Bai Jamjuree ExtraLight Regular (BaiJamjuree-ExtraLight.ttf)

GSUB

sinf

If there is a feature subs, then the sinf feature should be there, too. Otherwise InDesign will mark it not existing.

There is a subs feature in the font, but the sinf is missing. Please investigate.
